        Angular -Front End Development


        basic command

        1. to create project - ng new project-name / ng new project-name --routing

        2. to run a project - ng serve --open

        3. to create component - ng g c component-name

        4. to create services - ng g s service-name


                Basic Concepts

        1. Component - to create {html , css , ts file}  root Componet, AppComponent

        2. Module - to add Libraries to the project - root module -AppModule

        3. Data Binding - data sharing between html and ts

            3.1  One Way Binding
               
                3.1.1 Component to view

                    3.1.1.1 String Interpolation : Syntax- {{variable-name}}
                  
                    3.1.1.2 Property Binding: [attribute]="variable-name"
                
                3.1.2  view to component

                    3.1.2.1 Event Binding: (event)="functioncall()"

                    3.1.2.2 Event Binding Using Servent: (event)="function-call(servent)"

                    3.1.2.3 Template referencing variable  - syntax: #variable-name
            
            3.2 Two way Binding   
               
                3.2 -Using ngModel- Import FormsModule in AppModule,
                syntax:[(ngModel)]="variable-name" if it used in form tag set name attribute 

        4. To setup path for a component : defined in App Routing Module
        syntax: (path:'',component:componentClassName)

        5.Dependancy Injection - to share data between classes

        6.Angular Services - for reduntant data or reusable data

        7.ngSubmit - to to submit entire form  syntax: (ngSubmit)="function-call"
        
        8. Angular Forms:-

            8.1  Template Driven Forms - First design html
            8.2  Model Driven Forms - first create in ts
                8.2.1 Reactive Forms - Add Validation : ReactiveFormsModule
                    - form group- FormBuilder dependancy inject, form array, form control


